      "description": "Available is a 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant and a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission. This example is mechanically sound, with a recently addressed VANOS system and reinforced rear subframe mounting points to ensure structural integrity under lateral load. The factory variable M differential lock provides excellent traction out of corners, while the suspension geometry remains true with refreshed bushings and dampers. The throttle response is sharp across the powerband thanks to the individual throttle bodies. Finished in Titanium Silver, this M3 represents a balanced performance machine ready for the spirited driver who values mechanical provenance and chassis dynamics over a garage-queen pedigree.",
